"Unit Converter is a simple, user friendly unit converter. It has the most common units of measure and allows creating a favorite list for commonly used conversions. The preference menu allows for customizing the look and feel of the application.
Bug reports and feature suggestions are welcome.
Email: wopnersoft@gmail.com Website: http://wopnersoft.blogspot.com"

* This converter uses the SI Decimal/IEC Binary prefix naming convention. See http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Binary_prefix for an explanation and examples (i.e. kilo vs. Kibi, etc…).
* This converter uses the JEDEC Memory Standards naming convention (i.e. kilo is 1024 (2^10), mega is 2^20). See http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JEDEC_memory_standards for more information.
